  "playingCareerSummary": "Arguably the greatest all-rounder in cricket history: 166 Tests (13,289 runs at 55.37, 292 wickets), 328 ODIs (11,579 runs, 273 wickets). Played for Royal Challengers Bangalore (2008-2010) and Kolkata Knight Riders (2011-2015) in the IPL — won the 2012 and 2014 titles as a player.",
